body:
I'm using Icarus Verilog 12.0 (devel), running on WSL2, compiled directly from the head of the github repository, and I've pared my code down to a very small testcase:

```
module struct_assert_test;

struct packed
{
  logic a,b;
} s;

assign s.a = 1;
assign s.b = 0;
assign s.c = 1;

endmodule
```
I'm assigning values to the two fields (a and b) that exist in the structure s, and then I'm assigning a value to a field that does not exist.  Rather than throwing a syntax error or giving a warning about not being able to find that field, I get an assertion failure:

```
wlye@AMR-BU-L02782:~/foton$ iverilog -g2012 struct_assert_test.sv
struct_assert_test.sv:10: assert: elab_net.cc:640: failed assertion member
Aborted
wlye@AMR-BU-L02782:~/foton$
```

The assertion that is being thrown is
```
ivl_assert(*this, member);
```
which seems to make sense, however I am 99.5% unfamiliar with the code base so I would be extremely hesitant to propose an actual fix.

